This paper discusses wireless powered communication networks (WPCNs), which are a subfield of wireless networking. The paper specifically focuses on optimizing the throughput of a system composed of an access point and two battery-powered devices. This falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT), as well as systems and control (cs.SY) due to the need to consider the batteries' evolution. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of optimization techniques (cs.MA) and the potential for multimedia applications (cs.MM) in WPCNs.
